{"type":"message","id":"9ec28c7f","parentId":"ed88a9e6","timestamp":"2026-04-17T03:34:27.423Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"It seems there was an issue with fetching the latest AI news from Web using Brave Search API. This appears to be due to a missing API key.\n\nTo resolve this, you'll need to configure the Brave Search API key in your OpenClaw setup:\n\n1. **Run `openclaw configure --section web`** to store the API key.\n2. Alternatively, set the `BRAVE_API_KEY` environment variable for an automated configuration.\n\nOnce configured correctly, I can fetch and summarize the latest AI news from last 24 hours focusing on LLMs (Large Language Models), RL (Reinforcement Learning), diffusion models, VLM (Vision-Language Models), and robotics. Then, I'll provide a concise summary with explanations of their importance.\n"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"qwen-local:latest","usage":{"input":8441,"output":155,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":8596,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1776396867420}}
